column10: Car was yielding to allow me to cross in the crosswalk at the Glade Dr/Charterhouse Cir intersection. Fairfax Connector bus driver (Route 553) used the right shoulder to pass the yielding car, and drove through the crosswalk where I was still crossing.
Car stopped to let my kids and I cross but the car behind her was going around the shoulder. If the 1st car (that stopped) didn't honk, car would have hit my son.
Car crashed into another car who yielded for pedestrians in crosswalk. Cars travel too fast on this road and do not pay attention to all the pedestrians and cyclists.

This is for car 2 of 2: Two cars came into the bike lane at high speed to park. They blocked the bike lane. I had to walk on the road with speeding cars approaching and passing me by crossing the double yellow.

An Asian woman in a white Mercedes speeding dangerously to get her child to school and crossing the double yellow into the opposite lane and the single white into the protected bike lane to maximize her speed. She does this on a daily basis.
Two cars came into the bike lane at high speed to park. They blocked the bike lane. I had to walk on the road with speeding cars approaching and passing me by crossing the double yellow.
This is a daily issue.  Both AM and PM.  Drivers speed 10+ mph over speed limit, fail to stay out of bike lane, and often are holding a phone/drink/etc.
You show two crosswalks there is only one on Charterhouse and  Glade
Driver failed to stop, despite us being halfwy thru the crosswalk; didn't even slow down.
Driver didn't stop when we walked across Glade Dr and Charterhouse in Reston VA.  This is a bad intersection and needs to be improved for safety reasons.
Cars rarely stop for pedestrians here
Asian female in white Mercedes SUV speeding dangerously and crossing double yellow into opposite lane and solid white into protected bike lane. She does this on a daily basis.
Near miss while crossing at crosswalk. Driver did not see me and my dog in the middle of the crosswalk.
column21: A flashing light at this crosswalk would help pedestrians cross safely.
